<topic id="sharepoint-connection">
  <title>Integration with Microsoft SharePoint</title>
  <prolog>
    <metadata>
      <keywords>
        <indexterm>Databases<indexterm>Connections<indexterm>SharePoint</indexterm></indexterm></indexterm>
        <indexterm>SharePoint database connection</indexterm>
      </keywords>
    </metadata>
  </prolog>
  <body>
    <p><ph keyref="product"/> provides support for browsing and managing SharePoint connections in
      the <xref href="relational-database-explorer.dita#relational-database-explorer"
          ><uicontrol>Data Source Explorer</uicontrol> view</xref>. You can easily create new
      resources on the repository, copy and move them using contextual actions or the drag and drop
      support, or edit and transform the documents in the editor. </p>
    <p>
      <note>You can access documents stored on SharePoint Online for Office 365 sites that use
        either <b>Cloud identity (default)</b> or <b>Federated identity (ADFS)</b> as
        the authentication method.</note>
      <note type="restriction">The SharePoint connection is only available in the Enterprise edition
        of <ph keyref="product"/>.</note>
    </p>
    <p>
      <fig>
        <title>SharePoint Connection</title>
        <image href="../img/sharepoint_connection.png"/>
      </fig>
    </p>
  </body>
